Business Briefs
Qual-Med Inc. changed its $300 million offer to buy Health
Net, from $70 million in cash and the balance in a note, to
an all-cash offer.
   ---
   Delta Air Lines created an Administrative Services
division and a Marketing, Development and Planning division
to consolidate and improve efficiency of operations.
   ---
   Unimed Inc. agreed to allow LecTec Corp. to develop a
transdermal drug delivery system for its drug Marinol, an
anti-nausea treatment for cancer patients.
   ---
   Checkpoint Systems Inc. received an initial order from
Kmart Corp. for the installation of 200 Electronic Article
Merchandising systems.